      <item>
        <title>The Difference Between Being Alone and Loneliness</title>
        <link>https://wirtaw.github.io/blog/en/blog/the-difference-between-being-alone-and-loneliness/</link>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Social isolation can affect your mental health if you are not used to spending time with yourself. However, even this can be adapted to and enjoyed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many thinkers over the centuries have emphasized the importance of coming to terms with this state. Michel de Montaigne once even wrote: &amp;quot;The greatest thing in the world is to know how to belong to yourself.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Solitude encourages the imagination and makes it possible for serious thoughts to appear in people&#39;s heads that go beyond the usual routine and force the convolutions to move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Loneliness, on the other hand, is a negative experience. Self-pity, thoughts of a wasted life, sadness torment. And if you are really interested in your self-development, then it does not hurt to turn this feeling into positive and constructive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first step to being happy alone with yourself is accepting the situation. You need to ask yourself questions, turning loneliness into a constructive pastime: what do I really value in life? What do I need most? What do I need to do with...? What&#39;s next?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The second step is to keep your mind and body in constant tone. You need your body to calm your brain. You need feelings to organize your thoughts. Do not feed yourself with empty chatter and empty dramatic thoughts that only worsen the situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don&#39;t have to run from anything. Instead of running away from what is, you should notice what is right under your nose. It sounds a bit complicated, but think about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Try starting a journal and writing down thoughts about what interests you. Write poetry. Download Duolingo and delve into some new language. Start writing your autobiography or a book. Visit a virtual museum. Learn something new through YouTube or take a course that will help accelerate your career growth and expand your competence. Anything.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Being happy alone with yourself is a constant striving to be better mentally, socially and emotionally for yourself and your loved ones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today&#39;s topic is a bit complicated, but relevant - no offense. And we will end it with a wise saying: &amp;quot;You cannot be lonely if you like the person you are alone with.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        <pubDate>Sun, 29 Dec 2024 20:44:16 +0000</pubDate>
        <dc:creator>Vladimir Poplavskij</dc:creator>
        <guid>https://wirtaw.github.io/blog/en/blog/the-difference-between-being-alone-and-loneliness/</guid>
      </item>
      
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
      
      <item>
        <title>Finding Inner Peace in a Crazy World</title>
        <link>https://wirtaw.github.io/blog/en/blog/finding-inner-peace-crazy-world/</link>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;One day you stop fussing and trying to prove something to someone, you look with a smile at the world around you with all its madness, you don&#39;t rush to please people, you don&#39;t rush to give advice or judge or save anyone, you stop answering calls from people who haven&#39;t admired or interested you for a long time, you look at the sky more than at who is busy with what and how they live, you remember what inspires you regardless of the circumstances, you don&#39;t apologize, you don&#39;t explain, you don&#39;t argue, you don&#39;t waste time on the uninteresting and temporary, and you discover incredible peace and many things that you didn&#39;t notice before in the pursuit of meeting someone&#39;s ideas or meeting someone&#39;s expectations.  Comfort within is more precious than any temptations of temporary pleasure. More precious than any temporary people and temporary things. Everything you like is personal, and the personal belongs only to the person you see in the mirror. The rest is empty speculation and conjecture of those who are trying to see something else in you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are your own best ally in how to be yourself and be happy in this crazy world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;em&gt;Tatiana Marach&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        <pubDate>Sun, 29 Dec 2024 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        <dc:creator>Vladimir Poplavskij</dc:creator>
        <guid>https://wirtaw.github.io/blog/en/blog/finding-inner-peace-crazy-world/</guid>
